<subSubSection id="D49365161360541AFF63FCC0721FE205" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="9C36369D1360541AFF63FCC0721FE205" blockId="17.[151,1436,258,895]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="AEFDEA8F1360541AFF63FCC0775DE221" bold="true" box="[199,315,834,859]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species can readily be distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="5B894D1E1360541AFBBCFCC072FDE221" box="[1048,1179,834,859]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Evacanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AEFDEA8F1360541AFBBCFCC072FDE221" box="[1048,1179,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Evacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the subcontinent by the unpolished, wrinkled disc of the crown and by the peculiar shape of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
